original: Engellau, Gunnar Ludvig, civilingenjör, direktör, Trollhättan, f. 11/11/07 i Sthlm av adv. Ivar E. o. Hulda Lin-dequist. G. 33 m. Margit Höckert. Barn: John-Jakob f. 34, Christina 36, Birgitta 39, Margita 41, Caroline 43. — Stud :ex. v. norra real i Sthlm 26, utex. fr. KTH 31._ Anst. v. SJ hu-vudverkst. i Gbg, Örebro o. Sthlm 32-34, chef f. planerings- o. tidsstud:-avd. v. A-B Motala Verkst. 35-36, inköps- O’, försäljn :chef där 37-39, tekn. försäljn :chef v. Elektrolux i Sthlm o. Motala 39-43, verkst. dir. f. Sv. Flygmotor A-B ’S’ed. 43.
translated: Engellau, Gunnar Ludvig, engineer, director, Trollhättan, born on November 11, 1907 in Stockholm to lawyer Ivar E. and Hulda Lindequist. Married in 1933 to Margit Höckert. Children: John-Jakob born in 1934, Christina in 1936, Birgitta in 1939, Margita in 1941, Caroline in 1943. Education: graduated from Norra Real in Stockholm in 1926, graduated from KTH in 1931. Employed at SJ main workshop in Gothenburg, Örebro, and Stockholm from 1932-1934, head of planning and time study department at A-B Motala Verkst. from 1935-1936, procurement and sales manager from 1937-1939, technical sales manager at Elektrolux in Stockholm and Motala from 1939-1943, managing director of Swedish Flygmotor A-B 'S'ed in 1943.
